<div class="bg-gray-100">
    <!-- Introductory Section -->
    <div class="bg-blue-100 flex items-center p-8 w-full">
        <div class="w-1/2 pr-4">
            <h1 class="text-gray-800 text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Depression</h1>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                Feeling depressed does not always mean a person has a mental health condition. Many people occasionally feel low or sad from time to time. But when depression becomes frequent, out of proportion to a situation, or persists after the situation is over, it can be a sign of a depressive disorder.
            </p>
            <button id="view-faqs-button" class="text-blue-700 border border-blue-700 px-6 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
                View FAQs
            </button>
        </div>
        <div class="w-1/2">
            <img src="https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/depressed-man-sitting-on-floor-600nw-2231768289.jpg" alt="Depression visual" class="rounded-lg w-full h-auto object-cover">
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What is Depression Block -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 text-gray-800 p-8 w-full min-h-64">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">What is Depression?</h2>
        <p>Depression is a mood disorder that causes a persistent feeling of sadness and loss of interest. It affects how you feel, think, and behave and can lead to a variety of emotional and physical problems.</p>
        <p>When a person is depressed, it can interfere with daily life and reduce their ability to function normally. Symptoms may include changes in appetite, sleep disturbances, fatigue, difficulty concentrating, and feelings of hopelessness or worthlessness.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Reflecting Section -->
    <div class="bg-gray-700 text-white p-8 shadow-md mb-0">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Reflect</h2>
        <p class="mb-6 text-lg">Distracting oneself from depressive feelings may provide temporary relief, but addressing them directly can help identify effective coping strategies and promote long-term well-being.</p>

        <!-- Reflective Questions -->
        <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="w-full text-left bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded-lg flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <span class="font-semibold">What specific situations or events tend to trigger depression?</span>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-2xl">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden mt-2 text-gray-200">
                <p>Depression often arises from situations such as loss of a loved one, job loss, relationship breakdowns, or significant life changes. Financial difficulties or chronic illnesses can also lead to feelings of hopelessness and sadness. Identifying these triggers can help in understanding patterns and seeking appropriate support.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="w-full text-left bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded-lg flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <span class="font-semibold">How do individuals typically respond when they start to feel depressed?</span>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-2xl">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden mt-2 text-gray-200">
                <p>When depression begins to surface, the initial response may include withdrawal from social activities, decreased motivation, and reduced energy levels. Individuals may also experience changes in appetite and sleep patterns, leading to further feelings of fatigue and isolation. Recognizing these responses is important for seeking help and implementing coping strategies.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-4">
            <div class="w-full text-left bg-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded-lg flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <span class="font-semibold">What coping strategies have proven effective in managing depression?</span>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-2xl">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="hidden mt-2 text-gray-200">
                <p>Journaling can be an effective tool for processing thoughts and emotions related to depression. Writing about feelings often provides a different perspective, making them feel less overwhelming. Engaging in physical activities like yoga or running can help release built-up tension and improve mood. Additionally, discussing feelings with trusted friends or family members can offer comfort and understanding.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Breathing Exercise Section -->
    <div class="bg-blue-50 flex items-center p-8 w-full shadow-md">
        <div class="w-1/2 pr-4">
            <h1 class="text-gray-800 text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Breathe</h1>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Take a moment for yourself—engage in our guided breathing exercises to calm your mind and ease depression. Feel the weight lift as you breathe in peace and breathe out tension.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-1/2 pl-4 text-center">
            <img src="https://png.pngtree.com/png-vector/20230803/ourmid/pngtree-deep-breathing-clipart-calm-happy-young-woman-in-meditation-in-clouds-vector-png-image_6868038.png" alt="Breathing Exercise" class="mb-4 mx-auto rounded-md shadow-lg">
            <button id="try-breathing-button" class="text-blue-700 border border-blue-700 px-6 py-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200">
                Try Breathing Exercise
            </button>
        </div>

        <!-- Breathing Exercise Modal/Card -->
