                <h2 class="text-gray-800 text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-1">Knees to Chest Pose</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm text-center">Knees to Chest Pose may reduce lower back pain and could be calming when experiencing symptoms of anxiety and depression.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Pose 3: Humble Warrior -->
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-lg transition-transform transform hover:scale-105">
                <img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5a7aff15ccc5c54ba41f6454/1582481321814-103WYRMF2GU4JE7EVBIB/humble+warrior.jpg" alt="Humble Warrior" class="mb-2 mx-auto rounded-md h-32 object-cover">
                <h2 class="text-gray-800 text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-1">Humble Warrior</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm text-center">The Humble Warrior asana is a popular pose for increasing balance and guiding focus inward to the present moment.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Pose 4: Low Lunge -->
            <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded-lg shadow-lg transition-transform transform hover:scale-105">
                <img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/apepx3EDDwK6a99dQ0iWQEYdNrYB61X14CrKyKcRRHxUpFtikCI-YwjLrV-xlr50usDLmVgnVvegEH9nfQfob341JKbP-pBsPlVuJCzBJ4mD7BRfesgND0MCkxQ7dC5slMzTeqgl" alt="Low Lunge" class="mb-2 mx-auto rounded-md h-32 object-cover">
                <h2 class="text-gray-800 text-xl font-semibold text-center mb-1">Low Lunge</h2>
                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm text-center">The Low Lunge can help release tension in your hips and may improve mental focus.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Relaxation Videos & Audios -->
    <div class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-800 p-8 w-full shadow-md min-h-64">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Relaxation Videos & Audios</h2>
        <p>Watch and listen to relaxation videos to reduce depression:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
            <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xRxT9cOKiM8" class="text-blue-700 underline" target="_blank">10-Minute Guided Meditation</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VgdAcENXy84" class="text-blue-700 underline" target="_blank">Relaxing Nature Sounds</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    
    <!-- FAQs Section -->
    <div id="faqs" class="faq-section bg-gray-50 shadow-md p-6 w-full rounded-lg">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <!-- FAQ 1 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">What are the symptoms of depression?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>The symptoms of depression vary from person to person but often include a pervasive low mood, a sense of emptiness, or a loss of interest in activities. Physical symptoms can include fatigue, sleep disturbances (such as insomnia or oversleeping), and appetite changes, which might lead to weight gain or loss. Emotional symptoms often include feelings of guilt, worthlessness, or helplessness, as well as irritability. In severe cases, individuals may struggle with suicidal thoughts or behaviors. Recognizing these symptoms is an essential first step toward seeking help and initiating treatment.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 2 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">What causes depression?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Depression can result from a combination of factors, including genetics, environmental stress, and life experiences. A family history of depression increases the risk, suggesting a genetic predisposition. Stressful life events, such as the loss of a loved one, financial difficulties, or relationship issues, can also trigger depression. Additionally, chemical imbalances in the brain involving neurotransmitters like serotonin and dopamine are known to play a role in the development of depressive symptoms.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 3 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">Can lifestyle changes help manage depression?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>Yes, lifestyle changes can significantly help in managing depression, although they are often most effective when used alongside professional treatment. Regular physical activity, such as walking or yoga, has been shown to release endorphins, the body’s natural mood elevators, and can help reduce depressive symptoms. A balanced diet that includes essential nutrients can also positively impact mental health. Maintaining a consistent sleep routine is crucial, as poor sleep can exacerbate depression.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ 4 -->
        <div class="faq-item mb-4 border-b border-gray-300">
            <div class="faq-question flex justify-between items-center cursor-pointer p-3 hover:bg-gray-200" onclick="toggleFAQ(this)">
                <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-800">When should I see my healthcare provider about depression?</h3>
                <span class="faq-arrow text-gray-700">▼</span>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-answer hidden p-3">
                <p>If you have symptoms of depression, see a healthcare provider or mental health professional. They can give you an accurate diagnosis and suggest treatment options.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    // Function to toggle FAQ visibility
function toggleFAQ(element) {
    const answer = element.nextElementSibling;
    answer.classList.toggle('hidden'); // Toggle visibility
    const arrow = element.querySelector('.faq-arrow');
    arrow.textContent = answer.classList.contains('hidden') ? '▼' : '▲'; // Change arrow direction
}

// Start breathing exercise
document.getElementById('try-breathing-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
    const exerciseCard = document.getElementById('exerciseCard');
    exerciseCard.classList.remove('hidden');

    let timeLeft = 120; // Total duration of the exercise in seconds
    const timerDisplay = document.getElementById('timer');
    const instruction = document.getElementById('instruction');
    const breathingDuration = 4; // Seconds for inhale/exhale
    let inhale = true;

    timerDisplay.textContent = timeLeft;

    // Update breathing every second
    const countdown = setInterval(function() {
        timeLeft--;
        timerDisplay.textContent = timeLeft;

        if (timeLeft % 8 === 0) { // Every 8 seconds (4s inhale + 4s exhale)
            instruction.textContent = inhale ? "Inhale" : "Exhale";
            inhale = !inhale; // Toggle inhale/exhale
        }

        if (timeLeft <= 0) {
            clearInterval(countdown);
            instruction.textContent = "Great job! You're done!";
            document.getElementById('animation-circle').classList.add('hidden'); // Optionally hide circle at the end
        }
    }, 1000);
});

// Close breathing exercise
document.getElementById('closeExercise').addEventListener('click', function() {
    document.getElementById('exerciseCard').classList.add('hidden');
    clearInterval(countdown); // Clear the interval when closing
});

// Event listener for the FAQs button
document.getElementById('view-faqs-button').addEventListener('click', function() {
    const faqsSection = document.getElementById('faqs'); // Get the FAQs section
    
    // Scroll to the FAQs section smoothly
    faqsSection.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
});
// for horizontal scroll
const carousel = document.getElementById('carousel');
const leftButton = document.getElementById('leftButton');
const rightButton = document.getElementById('rightButton');

let scrollAmount = 0;

rightButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    scrollAmount += carousel.clientWidth * 0.6;
    carousel.scrollTo({
        left: scrollAmount,
        behavior: 'smooth'
    });
});

leftButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
    scrollAmount -= carousel.clientWidth * 0.6;
    carousel.scrollTo({
        left: scrollAmount,
        behavior: 'smooth'
    });
});
</script>